title: Anthropology and You
description: "We have all heard the phrase “Never judge a book by its cover”. Unfortunately, this phrase does not apply when discussing someone’s physical appearance...For this project, I wanted to take a deeper look into my own perception of self, how the world perceives me, and why I look the way I do. As a woman, I was socialized at a young age to care deeply about my appearance. The first thing people look at when they see me is my skin color and my hair. I am a Black woman with kinky, curly hair."
